{"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20"]]},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (29 min)","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc20\/10027","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10027-Modern-cell-configuration","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"Discover new techniques for configuring collection view and table view cells to quickly build dynamic interfaces in your app. Explore configuration types you can use to easily populate cells with content and apply common styles. Take advantage of powerful APIs to customize the appearance of cells for different states. Find out about patterns and best practices that simplify your code, eliminate bugs, and improve performance.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 12 brings new APIs to configure the content and styling of cells."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Getting-started-with-configurations","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Getting started with configurations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With iOS 14, standard cells should use the new content configurations:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["var content = cell.defaultContentConfiguration()","","content.image = UIImage(systemName: \"star\")","content.text = \"Hello WWDC!\"","","cell.contentConfiguration = content"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The cell’s "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uicollectionviewlistcell\/3600969-defaultcontentconfiguration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"always return a clean configuration (with nothing set on it)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"has a default styling, based on the cell and table view style"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The same approach is used for any cell that supports configurations ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UITableViewCell"},{"type":"text","text":"s, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UICollactionViewcell"},{"type":"text","text":"s, ..), this is possible because these standard cell layouts and appearances are now available as independent pieces that can plug right into any cell or view that supports them."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Using configurations will let the system take care of the multiple states a cell can be in, for example:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"normal","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"highlighted","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"highlighted and selected","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"disabled"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"and more.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"What-are-configurations","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"What are configurations?"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Configurations describe the cell appearance for a specific state","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"applied to a view to render","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"composable","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"lightweight (inexpensive to create)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"built for performance"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Configuration-types","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Configuration types"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Two types:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Background Configuration"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"List Content Configuration","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Background configurations let you set things such as:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"background color"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"visual effect (blur)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"stroke"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"insets and corner radius","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"custom view","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"List Content configurations give you the standard layout for cells, headers, and footers:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"image","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"secondary text","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"layout metrics and behaviors"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can change configurations at will, for example within an animation","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Configuration-state","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Configuration state"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Configuration state represents the various inputs that you use to configure your cells and views: it’s a collection of all the different traits, states, and your own custom states wrapped together in one place."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Each cell, header and footer has its own configuration state","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Two Types:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"View configuration state","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Cell configuration state","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"View-configuration-state","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"View configuration state"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This state has:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"a trait collection"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"four different (boolean) states: highlighted, selected, disabled, focused"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"and a custom state: this is key value storage for you to add any extra states or data that you want to use when configuring your view","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Cell-configuration-state","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Cell configuration state"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cell configuration state has everything from the View configuration state plus the following extra states:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(boolean) editing, swiped, expanded"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Drag and drop states","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We can ask a new configuration by passing a new state:"}]},{"code":["let updatedConfiguration = configuration.updated(for: state)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By default these configurations update by themselves when we set a new configuration, thanks to the cell ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uicollectionviewcell\/3600428-automaticallyupdatescontentconfi","isActive":true},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uicollectionviewcell\/3600427-automaticallyupdatesbackgroundco","isActive":true},{"text":"  properties:","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"text":"in other words, when you set a background or content configuration on the cell, any time the cell’s configuration state changes it will automatically ask the configuration to return an updated version of itself and then reapply that new configuration back to the cell.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you’d like to do this manually instead, you can override the cell’s new function ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uicollectionviewcell\/3600950-updateconfiguration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":":","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"text":"this method is always called before your cell first displays and will be called again anytime the configuration state may have changed so you can configure your cell for the new state.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here’s an example that customizes the cell colors based on the state:"}]},{"code":["override func updateConfiguration(using state: UICellConfigurationState) {","    var content = self.defaultContentConfiguration().updated(for: state)","    ","    content.image = self.item.icon","    content.text = self.item.title"," ","    if state.isHighlighted || state.isSelected {","        content.imageProperties.tintColor = .white","        content.textProperties.color = .white","    }"," ","    self.contentConfiguration = content","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Background-and-content-configurations","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Background and content configurations"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Each cell has a default background and content configuration, however we can ask for a specific configuration just as easily:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"code":["var background = UIBackgroundConfiguration.listSidebarCell()","var content = UIListContentConfiguration.sidebarCell()"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Configurations are designed to be used with self-sizing cells where their height can be flexible depending on the exact configuration and environment","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Content configurations give you control over the layout margins (blue), and various padding properties (orange)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC20-10027-layout"}]}]}]},{"anchor":"Written-By","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Written By"},{"numberOfColumns":5,"type":"row","columns":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"zntfdr","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"size":1},{"content":[{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Federico Zanetello","anchor":"Federico-Zanetello"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributed Notes","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/zntfdr.dev","isActive":true}]}],"size":4}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Missing anything? Corrections? ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference","isActive":true}]},{"anchor":"Related-Sessions","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Related Sessions"},{"type":"links","style":"list","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC22-10072-Use-SwiftUI-with-UIKit","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10191-Deliver-a-great-playback-experience-on-tvOS","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10260-Focus-on-iPad-keyboard-navigation","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10026-Lists-in-UICollectionView","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10045-Advances-in-diffable-data-sources","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10097-Advances-in-UICollectionView","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10105-Build-for-iPad"]},{"type":"small","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Legal Notice","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"small","inlineContent":[{"text":"All content copyright © 2012 – 2024 Apple Inc. All rights reserved.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Swift, the Swift logo, Swift Playgrounds, Xcode, Instruments, Cocoa Touch, Touch ID, FaceID, iPhone, iPad, Safari, Apple Vision, Apple Watch, App Store, iPadOS, watchOS, visionOS, tvOS, Mac, and macOS are trademarks of Apple Inc., registered in the U.S. and other countries.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This website is not made by, affiliated with, nor endorsed by Apple.","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10027-modern-cell-configuration"]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC20","role":"sampleCode","title":"Modern cell configuration","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"references":{"WWDC20.jpeg":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDC20.jpeg"}],"identifier":"WWDC20.jpeg","alt":null,"type":"image"},"https://zntfdr.dev":{"url":"https:\/\/zntfdr.dev","title":"Blog","identifier":"https:\/\/zntfdr.dev","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Blog","type":"text"}],"type":"link"},"zntfdr":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/zntfdr.jpeg"}],"identifier":"zntfdr","alt":"Profile image of Federico Zanetello","type":"image"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/uikit/uicollectionviewlistcell/3600969-defaultcontentconfiguration":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uicollectionviewlistcell\/3600969-defaultcontentconfiguration","title":"defaultContentConfiguration()","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uicollectionviewlistcell\/3600969-defaultcontentconfiguration","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"defaultContentConfiguration()","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"link"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/zntfdr":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/zntfdr","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr","title":"Federico Zanetello (332 notes)","kind":"article","images":[{"identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg","type":"card"},{"identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg","type":"icon"}],"role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"Software engineer with a strong passion for well-written code, thought-out composable architectures, automation, tests, and more.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"WWDC Notes","role":"collection","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Contributions are welcome!","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributions are welcome!","type":"text"}],"type":"link"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10097-Advances-in-UICollectionView":{"title":"Advances in UICollectionView","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about new features of UICollectionView that make it easier to use and unlock powerful new functionality. We’ll show you how to use section snapshots with your diffable data source to create outlines that can expand and collapse, and introduce you to building lists with compositional layout to create UITableView-like interfaces with a collection view. And discover modern techniques for dequeuing cells and configuring their content and styling."}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10097-advances-in-uicollectionview","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10097-Advances-in-UICollectionView"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/uikit/uicollectionviewcell/3600428-automaticallyupdatescontentconfi":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uicollectionviewcell\/3600428-automaticallyupdatescontentconfi","title":"automaticallyUpdatesContentConfiguration","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uicollectionviewcell\/3600428-automaticallyupdatescontentconfi","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"automaticallyUpdatesContentConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"link"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/uikit/uicollectionviewcell/3600950-updateconfiguration":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uicollectionviewcell\/3600950-updateconfiguration","title":"updateConfiguration(using:)","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uicollectionviewcell\/3600950-updateconfiguration","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"updateConfiguration(using:)","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"link"},"zntfdr.jpeg":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/zntfdr.jpeg"}],"identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg","alt":null,"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10026-Lists-in-UICollectionView":{"title":"Lists in UICollectionView","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to build lists and sidebars in your app with UICollectionView. Replace table view appearance while taking advantage of the full flexibility of compositional layout. Explore modular layout options and find out how they can unlock more design options for your apps than ever before. Find out how to combine table view-like lists with custom compositional layouts inside of a single UICollectionView. Discover how to work with lists, create richer cells, and customize your layout to create a well-designed presentation of information within your app."}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10026-lists-in-uicollectionview","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10026-Lists-in-UICollectionView"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21-10191-Deliver-a-great-playback-experience-on-tvOS":{"type":"topic","title":"Deliver a great playback experience on tvOS","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Find out how you can use Apple TV’s redesigned playback interface to build great media experiences in your apps. Learn how the latest interface helps people access relevant controls and information while maintaining focus on content. We’ll show you how you can adopt AVPlayerViewController and other APIs for your tvOS app to help people find, play, and enjoy content."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10191-deliver-a-great-playback-experience-on-tvos","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10191-Deliver-a-great-playback-experience-on-tvOS"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC22-10072-Use-SwiftUI-with-UIKit":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc22-10072-use-swiftui-with-uikit","role":"sampleCode","title":"Use SwiftUI with UIKit","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to take advantage of the power of SwiftUI in your UIKit app. Build custom UICollectionView and UITableView cells seamlessly with SwiftUI using UIHostingConfiguration. We’ll also show you how to manage data flow between UIKit and SwiftUI components within your app."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC22-10072-Use-SwiftUI-with-UIKit"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null,"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21-10260-Focus-on-iPad-keyboard-navigation":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10260-focus-on-ipad-keyboard-navigation","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","title":"Focus on iPad keyboard navigation","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10260-Focus-on-iPad-keyboard-navigation","abstract":[{"text":"Improve the keyboard experience in your iPad and Mac Catalyst app. Discover how you can accelerate access to key features with the hardware keyboard, and navigate through your views and view controllers. Learn how to customize which elements are keyboard navigable, as well as how to customize the tab loop.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10105-Build-for-iPad":{"kind":"article","title":"Build for iPad","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10105-Build-for-iPad","abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to improve iPad apps to leverage the increased screen size and additional features of iPadOS, and help people accomplish more with their devices. Discover how you can build detailed multi-column layouts and integrate lists into your app with little adjustment to your existing code. We’ll also explore reducing modality within your views to make it easier to navigate your interface with fewer taps and touches.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10105-build-for-ipad","type":"topic"},"WWDC20-10027-layout":{"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC20-10027-layout","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDC20-10027-layout.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/uikit/uicollectionviewcell/3600427-automaticallyupdatesbackgroundco":{"titleInlineContent":[{"code":"automaticallyUpdatesBackgroundConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"}],"title":"automaticallyUpdatesBackgroundConfiguration","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uicollectionviewcell\/3600427-automaticallyupdatesbackgroundco","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uicollectionviewcell\/3600427-automaticallyupdatesbackgroundco","type":"link"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","title":"WWDC20","role":"collectionGroup","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC20-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC20.jpeg"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 12, Swift 5.3, iOS 14, macOS 11 (Big Sur), tvOS 14, watchOS 7."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"code":"WidgetKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"StoreKit Testing","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10045-Advances-in-diffable-data-sources":{"title":"Advances in diffable data sources","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Diffable data sources dramatically simplify the work involved in managing and updating collection and table views to create dynamic and responsive experiences in your apps. Discover how you can use section snapshots to efficiently build lists and outline collection views for iOS and iPadOS and provide support for implementing the sidebar in an iPad app. We’ll also show you how to simplify cell reordering using UICollectionViewDiffableDataSource to help you streamline your code and build app interfaces more quickly."}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10045-advances-in-diffable-data-sources","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10045-Advances-in-diffable-data-sources"},"https://github.com/zntfdr":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":"GitHub","type":"text"}],"title":"GitHub","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","type":"link"},"WWDC20-Icon.png":{"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC20-Icon.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDC20-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image"},"https://developer.apple.com/wwdc20/10027":{"checksum":null,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc20\/10027","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc20\/10027","type":"download"}}}